text: Nothofagus stylosa is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae (Southern beeches) family. It is endemic to West Papua (Indonesia). It was proposed to be renamed Trisyngyne stylosa in 2013. It is a Vulnerable species threatened by habitat loss. ==References== Category:Nothofagaceae Category:Endemic flora of Western New Guinea Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
